Package life.genny.qwandaq

Class Context

  • java.lang.Object
    • life.genny.qwandaq.CoreEntity
      • life.genny.qwandaq.Context
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    CoreEntityInterface, Serializable, Comparable<Object>, CreatedIntf
    @Entity
@QueryExclude
public class Context
extends CoreEntity
implements Serializable
    Context is the class for all entity contexts managed in the Qwanda library. A Context object is used as a means of supplying information about a question that assists in understanding what answer is required. This context information includes:
    • The name of the context class
    • The context unique code
    • The key String for this context e.g. "employee" or "footballer" this is saved in name field

    Contexts represent the major way of supplying info about a question that permits a source to make a full decision. Contexts are also used in message merging.
